3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20many%20people%2C%20joining%20a%20brand-new%20startup%20as%20a%20fresh%20graduate%20is%20a%20risk.%20Why%20take%20the%20road%20less%20traveled%20when%20you%20can%20stick%20to%20the%20tried-and-tested%20path%20of%20joining%20a%20big%20company%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20felt%20right.%20I%20was%20starting%20my%20career%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202020%2C%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20I%20was%20living%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20people%20were%20dying%20every%20day.%20I%20could%20smell%20the%20ashes%20in%20the%20air%20from%20the%20cremations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20then%20that%20life%20really%20is%20short.%20I%20could%20die%20at%20any%20time%2C%20and%20when%20that%20happens%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20feel%20regret%20over%20not%20taking%20a%20risky%20but%20more%20exciting%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20four%20years%20at%20Warp%2C%20where%20I%20cycled%20through%20a%20variety%20of%20roles.%20I%20started%20out%20as%20an%20engineer%2C%20switched%20to%20marketing%2C%20and%20then%20ran%20the%20company's%20product%20and%20sales.%20I%20presented%20at%20board%20meetings%20every%20month%20and%20jumped%20on%20calls%20with%20our%20investors%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-got-rich-on-figma-ipo-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFigma%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20Dylan%20Field%2C%20every%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20a%20lot%20at%20Warp.%20That%20experience%20proved%20to%20be%20formative%20when%20I%20cofounded%20my%20own%20AI%20startup%2C%20Flint%2C%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7b53ea5-aa8c-4c63-9f9f-6ce6e494aba0%5C%22%3EBeing%20a%20founder%20is%20really%2C%20really%20hard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20founder%2C%20you%20are%20basically%20the%20startup's%20chief%20rejection%20officer.%20You%20are%20taking%20the%20brunt%20of%20rejections%20from%20sales%20prospects%2C%20recruits%2C%20and%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlint%20is%20an%20AI%20tool%20that%